cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper deals with machine translation, specifically for medical data, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of different training methods and models, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The evaluation metrics used in the paper, such as BLEU and METEOR, are commonly used in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential real-life implementation of the machine translation system in telemedicine, which involves the use of technology in healthcare, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible sub-category.
